Quote:  There was no shortage of volunteers for the 1056-man Kayforce that 50 years ago tomorrow sailed from Wellington to fight alongside other units from the Commonwealth in the Korean War... After only three months of training, the 16th Field Regiment and a number of smaller, ancillary units, known collectively as Kayforce, sailed on December 10, 1950, on the troopship Ormonde, arriving in Pusan on New Year's Eve and going into action against North Korea and its Chinese ally less than four weeks later.
