Quote:  Ever since they left New Zealand on December 10, 1950, to uphold the cause of the United Nations in repelling aggression, the members of K Force have maintained the traditions established by the N.Z. Expeditionary Forces in the First and Second World Wars ... Originally composed of the 16th. Field Regiment, R.N.Z.A., totalling 1000 men with 1st reinforcements, K Force has since been augmented by signalling, engineering, and A.S.C. units, making a combined total of 1668 New Zealanders now serving in Korea.
